text: I always learn from @Bob_Wachter on #COVID__19 but this tweetorial applying Bayesian reasoning to interpreting coronavirus testing is especially good. https://t.co/5JtZGtekdC
True to form, Donald G. McNeil gives a clear-eyed and at times startling description of the reality of #COVID__19 in life-long virus hunter Dr. Peter Pilot. https://t.co/dfj0E1TVEe
RT @HelenBranswell: CanSino reported on its Phase 1 #Covid19 vaccine trial in Lancet. Detail is terrific. Bravo for reporting vaccine data.…

Concerning- using malaria drugs to treat #COVIDー19: “One of the findings ... seems hard to ignore: that the drugs increase the risk of dangerous disturbances in heart rhythms.” https://t.co/Mj08FEWujK

Learning about spread- “superspreader” events and sites linked to #COVID19 infections and more serious clinical outcomes.  Talking, especially loudly, & singing implicated in spreading events. https://t.co/B7PqDMeoHB

I did miss this, and it is a must-read: Harold Varmus (& impressive colleagues) focus on increasing our knowledge and our ability to control #COVID19 using molecular epidemiology. https://t.co/WTU83O4eUz
Promising- a diagnostic that is  easy to run: “STOPCovid” With Crispr, a Possible Quick Test for the Coronavirus - The New York Times https://t.co/7LpJYwqw7b

20 years of investments ⁦@gatesfoundation now keenly focused on #COVID19. ⁩ ⁦@BillGates⁩ has emerged as a champion of science-backed solutions to addressing the coronavirus pandemic - The Washington Post https://t.co/7U3BJuzVAR
